  "prompt": "What are sticker packs in criminal case and how are they useful in the game?",
  "response": "In **Criminal Case**, **sticker packs** are collectible items that players can obtain by completing certain tasks or purchasing them with in-game currency or real money. Stickers often feature characters, objects, or scenes from the game and are part of the game's collectible system. Here's how they are useful:\n\n1. **Progress in the Game**:  \n   Stickers are often required to complete specific tasks or objectives in the game. For example, some cases or achievements might require you to collect certain stickers to advance.\n\n2. **Unlocking Content**:  \n   Collecting full sets of stickers can unlock special rewards, such as exclusive outfits, decorations, or other in-game items.\n\n3. **Customization**:  \n   Stickers can be used to customize your profile or office in the game, adding a personal touch and showcasing your progress.\n\n4. **Event Participation**:  \n   During special events or challenges, collecting specific stickers might be a key requirement to earn rewards or participate fully.\n\n5. **Trade or Exchange**:  \n   In some versions of the game, stickers can be traded or exchanged with other players or used in specific in-game mechanics to gain advantages.\n\nOverall, sticker packs add an extra layer of engagement and reward for players who enjoy collecting and completing sets in addition to solving cases.",
